    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "sometimes i look in the mirror and i don't even recognize the person looking back. it's like the real me—the one with the dreams and the spark—died decades ago. now i'm just walking around in this shell, a ghost of who i was supposed to be. just a hollow body going through the motions. it feels so heavy, just being a corpse that hasn't realized it's dead yet.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
